message.content: Lithobates blairi, commonly known as the Plains leopard frog, is a species of frog found in North America. It has a green or brownish-green color with dark spots and stripes on its skin. The skin has a smooth, slimy texture. The body and head of the frog are relatively proportional, with a rounded snout. It has a webbed hind feet, with flexible toes that aid in jumping and swimming. This species is commonly found in grasslands, wetlands, and prairies, and can be heard making a "chuckling" sound during mating season. Their diet consists of insects, spiders, and small invertebrates.
